hwWlanGlobalManagement.name: hwWlanGlobalManagement

revisions.description: The MIB module defines the ap update operation.
V1.04, Add the ApGroup Statistics info nodes.
V1.03, Add the hwWlanServiceNormalAPCount and hwWlanApCount info nodes.
V1.02, Add the backup license info nodes.
V1.01, Add the description of mib nodes.

hwWlanAccessMaxApNumber.name: hwWlanAccessMaxApNumber
hwWlanAccessMaxApNumber.description: This object indicates the maximum number of APs.

hwWlanAccessMaxStaNumber.name: hwWlanAccessMaxStaNumber
hwWlanAccessMaxStaNumber.description: This object indicates the maximum number of STAs connected to an AC.

hwWlanCurJointApNum.name: hwWlanCurJointApNum
hwWlanCurJointApNum.description: This object indicates the number of APs currently connected to an AC.

hwWlanCurAssocStaNum.name: hwWlanCurAssocStaNum
hwWlanCurAssocStaNum.description: This object indicates the number of associated users on an AC.

hwWlanCurAuthSuccessStaNum.name: hwWlanCurAuthSuccessStaNum
hwWlanCurAuthSuccessStaNum.description: This object indicates the total number of online STAs on an AC.

hwWlanReassocSuccessTimes.name: hwWlanReassocSuccessTimes
hwWlanReassocSuccessTimes.description: This object indicates the number of successful roaming times on an AC.

hwWlanCurAssoc2gStaNum.name: hwWlanCurAssoc2gStaNum
hwWlanCurAssoc2gStaNum.description: This object indicates the total number of 2.4G users on an AC.

hwWlanCurAssoc5gStaNum.name: hwWlanCurAssoc5gStaNum
hwWlanCurAssoc5gStaNum.description: This object indicates the total number of 5G users on an AC.

hwWlanDualBandStaNum.name: hwWlanDualBandStaNum
hwWlanDualBandStaNum.description: This object indicates the number of dual-band STAs.

hwWlanGlobalUpSpeed.name: hwWlanGlobalUpSpeed
hwWlanGlobalUpSpeed.description: This object indicates the upstream rate of the system (uplink throughput).

hwWlanGlobalDownSpeed.name: hwWlanGlobalDownSpeed
hwWlanGlobalDownSpeed.description: This object indicates the downstream rate of the system (downlink throughput).

hwWlanCurrentL3RoamStaCnt.name: hwWlanCurrentL3RoamStaCnt
hwWlanCurrentL3RoamStaCnt.description: This object indicates the count of current L3 roam stations.

hwWlanStaRateComplianceRate.name: hwWlanStaRateComplianceRate
hwWlanStaRateComplianceRate.description: This object indicates compliance ratio of the STA rate. Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: Rate > x (x = proportion of 12 Mbps STAs to the total number of STAs).

hwWlanStaSnrComplianceRate.name: hwWlanStaSnrComplianceRate
hwWlanStaSnrComplianceRate.description: This object indicates compliance ratio of STA signal-to-noise ratio (SNR). Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: SNR > x (x = 20 dB).

hwWlanStaResendRateComplianceRate.name: hwWlanStaResendRateComplianceRate
hwWlanStaResendRateComplianceRate.description: This object indicates compliance ratio of the STA retransmission rate (RR). Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: RR < x (x = 50%).

hwWlanStaDropRateComplianceRate.name: hwWlanStaDropRateComplianceRate
hwWlanStaDropRateComplianceRate.description: This object indicates compliance ratio of the STA packet loss rate (PLR). Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: PLR < x (x = 5%).

hwWlanStaComplianceRate.name: hwWlanStaComplianceRate
hwWlanStaComplianceRate.description: This object indicates the total STA compliance ratio.

hwStaSnrNoncompliance2gCnt.name: hwStaSnrNoncompliance2gCnt
hwStaSnrNoncompliance2gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of STAs whose 2.4G SNR fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: SNR > x (x = 20 dB).

hwStaRateNoncompliance2gCnt.name: hwStaRateNoncompliance2gCnt
hwStaRateNoncompliance2gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of STAs whose 2.4G rate fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: Rate > x (x = 12 Mbps).

hwStaResendRateNoncompliance2gCnt.name: hwStaResendRateNoncompliance2gCnt
hwStaResendRateNoncompliance2gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of STAs whose 2.4G retransmission rate (RR) fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: RR < x (x = 50%).

hwStaDropRateNoncompliance2gCnt.name: hwStaDropRateNoncompliance2gCnt
hwStaDropRateNoncompliance2gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of STAs whose 2.4G packet loss rate (PLR) fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: PLR < x (x = 5%).

hwStaThruputNoncompliance2gCnt.name: hwStaThruputNoncompliance2gCnt
hwStaThruputNoncompliance2gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of STAs whose 2.4G throughput fails to meet the compliance standard. (Here the throughput refers to a sum of the uplink and the downlink throughput.) Compliance standard: Throughput > x (x = 12 Mbps).

hwStaSnrNoncompliance5gCnt.name: hwStaSnrNoncompliance5gCnt
hwStaSnrNoncompliance5gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of STAs whose 5G SNR fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: SNR > x (x = 20 dB).

hwStaRateNoncompliance5gCnt.name: hwStaRateNoncompliance5gCnt
hwStaRateNoncompliance5gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of STAs whose 5G rate fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: Rate > x (x = 12 Mbps).

hwStaResendRateNoncompliance5gCnt.name: hwStaResendRateNoncompliance5gCnt
hwStaResendRateNoncompliance5gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of STAs whose 5G retransmission rate (RR) fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: RR < x (x = 50%).

hwStaDropRateNoncompliance5gCnt.name: hwStaDropRateNoncompliance5gCnt
hwStaDropRateNoncompliance5gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of STAs whose 5G packet loss rate (PLR) fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: PLR < x (x = 5%).

hwStaThruputNoncompliance5gCnt.name: hwStaThruputNoncompliance5gCnt
hwStaThruputNoncompliance5gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of STAs whose 5G throughput fails to meet the compliance standard. (Here the throughput refers to a sum of the uplink and the downlink throughput.) Compliance standard: Throughput > x (x = 12 Mbps).

hwWlanRfChannelUtilRateComplianceRate.name: hwWlanRfChannelUtilRateComplianceRate
hwWlanRfChannelUtilRateComplianceRate.description: This object indicates compliance ratio of the RF channel utilization. Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: Channel utilization < x (x = 70%).

hwWlanRfNoiseComplianceRate.name: hwWlanRfNoiseComplianceRate
hwWlanRfNoiseComplianceRate.description: This object indicates compliance ratio of the RF noise intensity. Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: Noise intensity < x (x = -80 dBm).

hwWlanRfChannelJamRateComplianceRate.name: hwWlanRfChannelJamRateComplianceRate
hwWlanRfChannelJamRateComplianceRate.description: This objects indicates compliance ratio of the RF interference ratio. Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: Interference ratio < x (x = 40%).

hwWlanRfResendRateComplianceRate.name: hwWlanRfResendRateComplianceRate
hwWlanRfResendRateComplianceRate.description: This objects indicate compliance ratio of the RF retransmission rate (RR). Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: RR < x (x = 50%).

hwWlanRfDropRateComplianceRate.name: hwWlanRfDropRateComplianceRate
hwWlanRfDropRateComplianceRate.description: This objects indicates compliance ratio of the RF packet loss rate (PLR). Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: PLR < x (x = 5%).

hwWlanRfComplianceRate.name: hwWlanRfComplianceRate
hwWlanRfComplianceRate.description: This object indicates the total RF compliance ratio.

hwWlanRfNoiseNoncompliance2gCnt.name: hwWlanRfNoiseNoncompliance2gCnt
hwWlanRfNoiseNoncompliance2gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of radios on which the 2.4G noise intensity fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: Noise intensity < x (x = -80 dBm).

hwWlanRfChannelUtilRateNoncompliance2gCn.name: hwWlanRfChannelUtilRateNoncompliance2gCnt
hwWlanRfChannelUtilRateNoncompliance2gCn.description: This object indicates the number of radios on which the 2.4G channel utilization fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: Channel utilization < x (x = 70%).

hwWlanRfLoadNoncompliance2gCnt.name: hwWlanRfLoadNoncompliance2gCnt
hwWlanRfLoadNoncompliance2gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of radios on which the 2.4G load fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: Number of online users < x (x = 40).

hwWlanRfChannelJamRateNoncompliance2gCnt.name: hwWlanRfChannelJamRateNoncompliance2gCnt
hwWlanRfChannelJamRateNoncompliance2gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of radios on which the 2.4G interference ratio fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: Interference ratio < x (x = 40%).

hwWlanRfNoiseNoncompliance5gCnt.name: hwWlanRfNoiseNoncompliance5gCnt
hwWlanRfNoiseNoncompliance5gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of radios on which the 5G noise intensity fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: Noise intensity < x (x = -80 dBm).

hwWlanRfChannelUtilRateNoncompliance5gCn.name: hwWlanRfChannelUtilRateNoncompliance5gCnt
hwWlanRfChannelUtilRateNoncompliance5gCn.description: This object indicates the number of radios on which the 5G channel utilization fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: Channel utilization < x (x = 70%).

hwWlanRfLoadNoncompliance5gCnt.name: hwWlanRfLoadNoncompliance5gCnt
hwWlanRfLoadNoncompliance5gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of radios on which the 5G load fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: Number of online users < x (x = 40).

hwWlanRfChannelJamRateNoncompliance5gCnt.name: hwWlanRfChannelJamRateNoncompliance5gCnt
hwWlanRfChannelJamRateNoncompliance5gCnt.description: This object indicates the number of radios on which the 5G interference ratio fails to meet the compliance standard. Compliance standard: Interference ratio < x (x = 40%).

hwWlanApNormalRatio.name: hwWlanApNormalRatio
hwWlanApNormalRatio.description: This object indicates the proportion of APs in normal and commit states to all APs. Unit: 0.01.

hwWlanApStaOnlineFailRateComplianceRate.name: hwWlanApStaOnlineFailRateComplianceRate
hwWlanApStaOnlineFailRateComplianceRate.description: This object indicates compliance ratio of the AP's STA access failure rate. Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: STA access failure rate < x (x = 20%) Access failure rate = (hwStaAccessRequestFailedCount+hwStaAuthenRequestFailedCount)/(hwStaAssocAndReAssocRequestCount+hwStaAuthenRequestCount).

hwWlanApStaOfflineRateComplianceRate.name: hwWlanApStaOfflineRateComplianceRate
hwWlanApStaOfflineRateComplianceRate.description: This object indicates compliance ratio of the AP's STA offline rate. Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: STA offline rate x (x = 20%) Offline rate = hwStaExceptionalOfflineCnt/hwStaAuthenRequestSuccessCount. Abnormal APs are those in fault, version mismatch, and type mismatch.

hwWlanApStaOnlineCntComplianceRate.name: hwWlanApStaOnlineCntComplianceRate
hwWlanApStaOnlineCntComplianceRate.description: This object indicates compliance ratio of the number of access STAs on an AP. Unit: 0.01 Compliance standard: Access STAs < x (x = 40). Access STAs refer to online STAs. Abnormal APs are those in fault, version mismatch, and type mismatch.

hwWlanApComplianceRate.name: hwWlanApComplianceRate
hwWlanApComplianceRate.description: This object indicates the total AP compliance ratio.

hwWlanServiceNormalAPCount.name: hwWlanServiceNormalAPCount
hwWlanServiceNormalAPCount.description: This object indicates the total of AP in service normal states.

hwWlanApCount.name: hwWlanApCount
hwWlanApCount.description: This object indicates the total of AP.

hwWlanOnlineStaCntHistoryTable.name: hwWlanOnlineStaCntHistoryTable
hwWlanOnlineStaCntHistoryTable.description: This table describes historical number of access users, which is counted every 1 min. The AC stores data in the latest 15 min.

hwWlanOnlineStaCntHistoryEntry.name: hwWlanOnlineStaCntHistoryEntry
hwWlanOnlineStaCntHistoryEntry.description: The index of this table is hwWlanOnlineStaCntTime.

hwWlanOnlineStaCntTime.name: hwWlanOnlineStaCntTime
hwWlanOnlineStaCntTime.description: This object indicates the count time. It is the index of the table.

hwWlanOnlineStaCnt.name: hwWlanOnlineStaCnt
hwWlanOnlineStaCnt.description: This object indicates the number of access users.

hwWlan2gOnlineStaCnt.name: hwWlan2gOnlineStaCnt
hwWlan2gOnlineStaCnt.description: This object indicates the number of users connected to the 2.4G radio.

hwWlan5gOnlineStaCnt.name: hwWlan5gOnlineStaCnt
hwWlan5gOnlineStaCnt.description: This object indicates the number of users connected to the 5G radio.

hwWlanSpeedHistoryTable.name: hwWlanSpeedHistoryTable
hwWlanSpeedHistoryTable.description: This table describes the historical effective throughput statistics, which is collected every 1 min. The AC stores data in the latest 15 min.

hwWlanSpeedHistoryEntry.name: hwWlanSpeedHistoryEntry
hwWlanSpeedHistoryEntry.description: The index of this table is hwWlanSpeedHistoryTime.

hwWlanSpeedHistoryTime.name: hwWlanSpeedHistoryTime
hwWlanSpeedHistoryTime.description: This object indicates the statistics collection time. It is the index of the table.

hwWlanUpSpeedHistory.name: hwWlanUpSpeedHistory
hwWlanUpSpeedHistory.description: This object indicates uplink effective throughput of the AC. Unit: Mbps.

hwWlanDownSpeedHistory.name: hwWlanDownSpeedHistory
hwWlanDownSpeedHistory.description: This object indicates downlink effective throughput of the AC.Unit: Mbps.

hwWlanApGroupStatisticsTable.name: hwWlanApGroupStatisticsTable
hwWlanApGroupStatisticsTable.description: This table collects statistics about 2G and 5G users in AP groups.

hwWlanApGroupStatisticsEntry.name: hwWlanApGroupStatisticsEntry
hwWlanApGroupStatisticsEntry.description: The index of this table is hwWlanApGpStatAPGroupName.

hwWlanApGpStatAPGroupName.name: hwWlanApGpStatAPGroupName
hwWlanApGpStatAPGroupName.description: This object indicates the name of an AP group. It is the index of the table.

hwWlanApGpStatCurAssoc2gStaNum.name: hwWlanApGpStatCurAssoc2gStaNum
hwWlanApGpStatCurAssoc2gStaNum.description: This object indicates the number of 2G users in an AP group.

hwWlanApGpStatCurAssoc5gStaNum.name: hwWlanApGpStatCurAssoc5gStaNum
hwWlanApGpStatCurAssoc5gStaNum.description: This object indicates the number of 5G users in an AP group.
